File: Human Settlements Director-General, Mbulelo Tshangana has been placed on special leave. (eNCA\Screenshot) JOHANNESBURG - Human Settlements director-general, Mbulelo Tshangana says the power to place him on special leave lies with President Cyril Ramaphosa and not with Minister Mmamoloko Kubayi. Tshangana has reportedly been placed on special leave by Minister Mmamoloko Kubayi. She has accused him of repeatedly defying her and failing to fulfill his duties as an accounting officer of the Human Settlements Department. READ: Human Settlements DG Tshangana placed on special leave He was sent on leave from Wednesday. Meanwhile, in a statement released by his office, Tshangana says a mediation process will be underway and leaks about him being placed on special leave undermine this process. The statement also further states that he will continue in his role as Human Settlements director-general until the mediation process is finalised by the presidency.